audit-b8: auto_bridge: drop spin_lock_bh before rtnl_lock in send-msg work

abm_do_work_send_msg() iterates two lists under spin_lock_bh(&abm_lock):

  (a) l2flow_list_msg_to_send  - safe, only calls in-atomic helpers
  (b) bridge_list_rtevent      - calls rtnl_lock() / rtmsg_ifinfo() per entry

(b) is broken: rtnl_lock() is a sleeping mutex (mutex_lock under the
hood), and taking a sleeping primitive while holding a bottom-half
spinlock is a "scheduling while atomic" bug. CONFIG_DEBUG_ATOMIC_SLEEP
flags it on every BREVENT_FDB_UPDATE that adds a brevent, which on a
busy bridge with frequent fdb churn is "every few seconds".

Fix (audit AB-07): splice bridge_list_rtevent into a function-local
list head while still holding abm_lock, drop the spinlock, then walk
the local list at sleep-capable context with rtnl_lock() per entry.
This preserves the original semantics:

  - the original code held abm_lock across BOTH list traversals, but
    nothing reads bridge_list_rtevent except this work item, so
    splicing under the lock and processing outside is equivalent
    from the producer's (abm_br_event) point of view: the producer
    list_add()s into bridge_list_rtevent under spin_lock_bh, and the
    splice atomically transfers ownership of every queued entry to
    the local list before any new producer can enqueue more.

The GFP_ATOMIC argument to rtmsg_ifinfo() also becomes GFP_KERNEL
since we are no longer in atomic context for that call.

Audit reference: AUDIT-auto_bridge.md (AB-07, sleep-in-atomic).

--- a/auto_bridge/auto_bridge.c	2026-05-05 12:59:00.314030184 +0000
+++ b/auto_bridge/auto_bridge.c	2026-05-05 13:01:30.019109725 +0000
@@ -107,6 +107,8 @@
 	if (!netlink_has_listeners(abm_nl, L2FLOW_NL_GRP)){
 		return;
 	}
+	LIST_HEAD(local_rtevent_list);
+
 	spin_lock_bh(&abm_lock);
 	//TODO : Need to limit the number of messages to sent while holding the lock.
 	list_for_each_safe(entry, tmp, &l2flow_list_msg_to_send){
@@ -134,19 +136,25 @@
 		}
 	}
 
-	list_for_each_safe(entry, tmp, &bridge_list_rtevent){
+	/* AB-07 (B8): rtnl_lock() is a sleeping mutex; cannot be taken under
+	 * spin_lock_bh(). Splice bridge_list_rtevent into a local list under
+	 * the spinlock, drop the spinlock, then iterate with rtnl_lock().
+	 */
+	list_splice_init(&bridge_list_rtevent, &local_rtevent_list);
+
+	spin_unlock_bh(&abm_lock);
+
+	list_for_each_safe(entry, tmp, &local_rtevent_list){
 		brtable_entry = container_of(entry, struct br_event_table, list_rtevent);
 		if (brtable_entry->brdev)
 		{
 			rtnl_lock();
-			rtmsg_ifinfo(RTM_NEWLINK, brtable_entry->brdev, 0, GFP_ATOMIC, 0, NULL);
+			rtmsg_ifinfo(RTM_NEWLINK, brtable_entry->brdev, 0, GFP_KERNEL, 0, NULL);
 			rtnl_unlock();
 		}
 		list_del(&brtable_entry->list_rtevent);
 		kmem_cache_free(brroute_cache, brtable_entry);
 	}
-
-	spin_unlock_bh(&abm_lock);
 }
 
